						               													<description>Description from the publisher:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Kann: le combat is a confrontation game for two players, inspired from Jules Verne's book &amp;quot;20.000 lieux sous les mers&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One plays the &amp;quot;Nautilus&amp;quot; submarine and its crew while his opponent plays the giant Squid.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Squid player wins if he meets any of these 3 conditions :&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     eat the captain of the Nautilus&amp;#10;     eat 3 crew member (out of 10)&amp;#10;     inflict 6 damages to the Nautilus&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Nautilus player wins if he cuts 5 tentacles (out of 6).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn, both player roll two dice and use them on their dashboard in order to trigger various actions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Squid can throw ink (an attack meant to deal damages to the Nautilus), gather anger (anger points can be used to influence subsequent dice), deploy or retract his tentacles.&amp;#10;Tentacles do hit the Nautilus when they reach it, and can capture a crew member when deployed inside. In order to be eaten, a captured crew member has to be brought back to the Squid's mouth by retracting the tentacle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Nautilus player can move his crew members, rescue a crew member fallen to the sea, improve his moral (moral can influence subsequent dice), repair damages, and attack the Squid with axes, harpoons, or electricity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
